Ethernet Cable
Up to 10Gbps Speed and Multi-shielded Cable

Cat7 network Ethernet cable could transmitting data at speed up to 10Gbps over 100m run of cable. It is made out of 4 shielded twisted pair (STP) of copper wires with two gold RJ45 connectors on each end. Compared to the Cat 6A/6/5 Ethernet cable, the additional shielding and improved quality in twisting of the wires provides better protection from crosstalk, noise, and interference that can degrade the signal quality.
